    <p>The central figure in The Life List is Brett Bohlinger, a woman whose comfortable life is upended by her mother's unconventional will. Brett's character arc is the focal point of the narrative, as she transforms from a complacent individual into someone willing to embrace uncertainty and pursue her true passions. The cast surrounding Brett serves to facilitate or hinder this transformation.</p>
